translated: Blomqvist, Georg Henning, civil engineer, Gothenburg, born December 13, 1894 in Högsjö, Västernorrl. 1st son of commissioner Gustaf B. and Helga Holmström. Married to Gunvor Reutervall in 1922. Children: Ragna born in 1924. He completed his high school education in Härnösand in 1914. He graduated from the Royal Institute of Technology (KTH) in 1917 and studied life chemistry at Fresenius Lab in Wiesbaden from 1921 to 1922. He worked as a operation engineer at A-B Difosfat in Trollhättan from 1918 to 1919 and at Skand. Grafitind. A-B from 1919 to 1921. He worked as an experimenter and later lab chief at Crescent Manufacturing Co. in Seattle from 1922 to 1925. He owned the company Kem. Kontrollbyrån in Stockholm from 1925 to 1927, and after the merger with Groths Kem. Byrå in 1927 to Kem. Kontr: byrån A-B he was employed there until 1932. He was the operation engineer at P. O. Stokkebye's Kvarn A-B in Gothenburg from then until his death. He has been a member of the Swedish Engineering Association since 1918.
